
You are a senior Jira backend + frontend engineer.

The project already has:
- Projects, Epics, Stories, Tasks, Subtasks, Bugs
- Task Estimation & Time Tracking fields (originalEstimate, remainingEstimate, timeSpent)

GOAL:
Implement FULL Jira-style Time Logging (8.2) functionality
without breaking existing estimation logic.

==================================================
STEP 1 — ANALYZE EXISTING IMPLEMENTATION
==================================================

1. Scan backend & frontend code.
2. Identify:
   - Existing log work APIs (if any)
   - Existing timeSpent / remainingEstimate usage
   - Where task status updates happen
3. DO NOT recreate existing logic.
4. Extend only where required.

==================================================
STEP 2 — DATA MODEL (LOG WORK ENTITY)
==================================================

Create a dedicated TimeLog (WorkLog) model.

Fields:
- issueId (Task | Subtask | Bug)
- issueType ("task" | "subtask" | "bug")
- userId
- timeSpent (minutes)
- logDate (YYYY-MM-DD)
- comment?
- startedAt? (for timer)
- endedAt? (for timer)
- createdAt
- updatedAt

Rules:
- One log entry = immutable time record
- Editing creates audit-safe updates
- Time is always stored in minutes

==================================================
STEP 3 — BACKEND API (NestJS)
==================================================

A) Manual Time Logging
POST /time-logs
{
  issueId,
  timeSpent,
  logDate,
  comment?
}

B) Timer-based Logging
POST /time-logs/start
POST /time-logs/stop

- Timer auto-calculates timeSpent
- Prevent multiple active timers per user

C) Edit Logged Time (Permission Based)
PUT /time-logs/:id

Rules:
- Admin → can edit/delete any log
- User → can edit/delete own logs only

D) Delete Logged Time
DELETE /time-logs/:id

Rules:
- Restore remainingEstimate correctly
- Recalculate parent hierarchy

==================================================
STEP 4 — TIME CONSISTENCY LOGIC
==================================================

When time is logged / edited / deleted:

1. Update issue.timeSpent
2. Recalculate remainingEstimate
3. Roll up time:
   Subtask → Task → Story → Epic
4. Prevent negative remaining time
5. Prevent logging beyond remaining estimate (unless admin)

==================================================
STEP 5 — DAILY & WEEKLY TIMESHEETS
==================================================

Implement:

GET /time-logs/timesheet?userId=&from=&to=

Response:
- Day-wise grouped logs
- Total time per day
- Total time per week
- Project-wise summary

Example:
{
  "2025-01-10": {
    "totalMinutes": 420,
    "entries": [...]
  }
}

==================================================
